    <string name="health_title">Why 80% / 20%?</string>
    <string name="health_body">Lithium batteries age fastest at the extremes. Staying roughly between 20% and 80% reduces voltage stress and heat — the two main causes of permanent capacity loss. An occasional full charge is fine (it helps the gauge calibrate), but sitting at 100% or draining to 0% every day measurably shortens battery lifespan. That\'s why WattFlow defaults to alerts at 80% and 20%.</string>
